Message.MsgText: Cannot modify destination mapping rule in enabled state.

Explanation.p: A destination mapping rule can be updated only when it is disabled.

OperatorResponse.p: Update the destination mapping rule after it has been disabled.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule state must not change when other updates to the rule are made.

Explanation.p: The destination mapping rule state can be updated only when no other updates are made.

OperatorResponse.p: Update the destination mapping rule state with no other updates.

Message.MsgText: Queue manager connection associated with destination mapping rule cannot be deleted.

Explanation.p: A queue manager connection can be deleted only when it is not associated with any destination mapping rules.

OperatorResponse.p: Delete the queue manager connection after it is no longer associated with any destination mapping rules.

Message.MsgText: MQ Connectivity could not connect to the ${IMA_SVR_COMPONENT_NAME}.

Explanation.p: A queue manager connection can only be added when MQ Connectivity is connected to the ${IMA_SVR_COMPONENT_NAME}.

OperatorResponse.p: Verify the server is running and try again.

Message.MsgText: ISMC API failed. API {0}. Reason {1}.

Explanation.p: A failure occurred while issuing an ISMC API.

OperatorResponse.p: Use the reason shown in the message to determine the cause of the failure and take appropriate action to rectify the problem.

Message.MsgText: Destination Mapping {0}. ISMC API failed. API {1}. Reason {2}.

Explanation.p: A failure occurred while issuing an ISMC API for a destination mapping rule.

OperatorResponse.p: Use the reason shown in the message to determine the cause of the failure and take appropriate action to rectify the problem.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule {0}. Queue manager connection {1}. ISMC API failed. API {2}. Reason {3}.

Explanation.p: A failure occurred while issuing an ISMC API for a destination mapping queue manager connection.

OperatorResponse.p: Use the reason shown in the message to determine the cause of the failure and take appropriate action to rectify the problem.

Message.MsgText: ISMC network error. API {0}. Reason {1}. This may be because the server is not running.

Explanation.p: An ISMC API call encountered a network error. This usually happens if the server is not running.

OperatorResponse.p: Check that the server is running. If it is, use the reason shown in the message to determine the cause of the failure and take appropriate action to rectify the problem.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule {0}. Queue manager connection {1}. ISMC API failed. API {2}. Reason {3}. Subscription name {4}. Managed queue name {5}.

Explanation.p: A persistent message was unable to be sent to ${IMA_PRODUCTNAME_SHORT} as the destination is not valid. This can happen when the destination mapping rule type is MQ topic subtree to ${IMA_PRODUCTNAME_SHORT} topic subtree and the message was published to a WebSphere MQ topic with more than 32 levels.

OperatorResponse.p: The persistent message should be removed from the WebSphere MQ managed queue associated with the WebSphere MQ subscription.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule {0}. Queue manager connection {1}. WebSphere MQ API failed. API {2}. Reason {3}.

Explanation.p: A failure occurred while issuing a WebSphere MQ API.

OperatorResponse.p: Use the reason code shown in the message to determine the cause of the failure and take appropriate action to rectify the problem.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule {0}. Queue manager connection {1}. Unable to connect to WebSphere MQ queue manager {2}. MQCONNX Reason {3}.

Explanation.p: A failure occurred while attempting to connect to a WebSphere MQ queue manager.

OperatorResponse.p: Use the reason code shown in the message to determine the cause of the failure and take appropriate action to rectify the problem.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule {0}. Queue manager connection {1}. Unable to open WebSphere MQ queue {2}. MQOPEN Reason {3}.

Explanation.p: A failure occurred while attempting to open a WebSphere MQ queue.

OperatorResponse.p: Use the reason code shown in the message to determine the cause of the failure and take appropriate action to rectify the problem.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule {0}. Queue manager connection {1}. Unable to open WebSphere MQ topic {2}. MQOPEN Reason {3}.

Explanation.p: A failure occurred while attempting to open a WebSphere MQ topic.

OperatorResponse.p: Use the reason code shown in the message to determine the cause of the failure and take appropriate action to rectify the problem.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule {0}. Queue manager connection {1}. Unable to subscribe to WebSphere MQ topic {2}. Subscription name {3}. MQSUB Reason {4}.

Explanation.p: A failure occurred while attempting to subscribe to a WebSphere MQ topic.

OperatorResponse.p: Use the reason code shown in the message to determine the cause of the failure and take appropriate action to rectify the problem.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule {0}. Queue manager connection {1}. Unable to subscribe to WebSphere MQ topic {2}. Subscription name {3}. Subscription exists with topic string ending {4}.

Explanation.p: A failure occurred while attempting to subscribe to a WebSphere MQ topic as a subscription with the same name exists with a different topic string.

OperatorResponse.p: Delete the subscription from the WebSphere MQ queue manager if it is no longer required.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule {0}. Queue manager connection {1}. Unable to put to WebSphere MQ queue {2}. MQPUT Reason {3}.

Explanation.p: A failure occurred while attempting to put a message to a WebSphere MQ queue.

OperatorResponse.p: Use the reason code shown in the message to determine the cause of the failure and take appropriate action to rectify the problem.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule {0}. Queue manager connection {1}. Unable to get PCF response from WebSphere MQ temporary dynamic reply queue {2}. MQGET Reason {3}.

Explanation.p: A failure occurred while attempting to get a PCF response from a WebSphere MQ temporary dynamic reply queue. MQRC_NO_MSG_AVAILABLE might indicate that the command server is not running on the WebSphere MQ queue manager.

OperatorResponse.p: Use the reason code shown in the message to determine the cause of the failure and take appropriate action to rectify the problem.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule {0}. Queue manager connection {1}. Unable to create ${IMA_PRODUCTNAME_SHORT} WebSphere MQ synchronization queue {2}. Reason {3}.

Explanation.p: A failure occurred while attempting to create a ${IMA_PRODUCTNAME_SHORT} WebSphere MQ synchronization queue.

OperatorResponse.p: Use the reason code shown in the message to determine the cause of the failure and take appropriate action to rectify the problem.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule {0}. Queue manager connection {1}. Unable to delete ${IMA_PRODUCTNAME_SHORT} WebSphere MQ synchronization queue {2}. Reason {3}.

Explanation.p: A failure occurred while attempting to delete a ${IMA_PRODUCTNAME_SHORT} WebSphere MQ synchronization queue.

OperatorResponse.p: Use the reason code shown in the message to determine the cause of the failure and take appropriate action to rectify the problem.

Message.MsgText: Invalid WebSphere MQ message. Message type {0}.

Explanation.p: A failure occurred while attempting to parse a WebSphere MQ message. An FFDC is generated with the message content.

OperatorResponse.p: Contact IBM support for further assistance.

Message.MsgText: Unable to allocate memory. {0} {1} byte(s) errno {2}.

Explanation.p: A failure occurred while attempting to allocate memory.

OperatorResponse.p: Examine the system memory resource. Use system tools to profile memory usage for the entire process.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule {0}. Queue manager connection {1}. Unable to allocate memory. {2} {3} byte(s) errno {4}.

Explanation.p: A failure occurred while attempting to allocate memory for a destination mapping queue manager connection.

OperatorResponse.p: Examine the system memory resource. Use system tools to profile memory usage for the entire process.

Message.MsgText: System API failed. API {0}. rc {1} errno {2}

Explanation.p: A failure occurred while issuing a system API.

OperatorResponse.p: Use the reason code shown in the message to determine the cause of the failure and take appropriate action to rectify the problem.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule {0}. Queue manager connection {1}. Connected to WebSphere MQ queue manager {2}.

Explanation.p: MQ Connectivity successfully connected to a WebSphere MQ queue manager.

OperatorResponse.p: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: Failed to parse monitoring request {0}: RC={1}.

Explanation.p: MQ Connectivity received a request for monitoring information but the request was unreadable.

OperatorResponse.p: Contact IBM support for further assistance.

Message.MsgText: The monitoring action {0} is not supported.

Explanation.p: MQ Connectivity received a request for monitoring information of a type that it does not provide.

OperatorResponse.p: Contact IBM support for further assistance.

Message.MsgText: ${IMA_PRODUCTNAME_SHORT} MQ Connectivity service is starting.

Explanation.p: The MQ Connectivity component of the ${IMA_PRODUCTNAME_SHORT} is starting.

OperatorResponse.p: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule {0}. Queue manager connection {1}. WebSphere MQ API failed. API {2}. Reason {3}. Length {4}.

Explanation.p: A failure occurred while issuing a WebSphere MQ API.

OperatorResponse.p: Use the reason code shown in the message to determine the cause of the failure and take appropriate action to rectify the problem.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule {0}. Queue manager connection {1}. Unable to define callback function for WebSphere MQ queue manager {2}. MQCB Reason {3}.

Explanation.p: MQ Connectivity was unable to define a callback function for the named queue manager and therefore cannot receive notification of queue manager state changes.

OperatorResponse.p: If the problem persists, contact IBM support for further assistance.

Message.MsgText: Rule index {0}. Unable to alter MaxMessages for subscription - {1}

Explanation.p: An attempt to alter MaxMessages for an active rule, failed.

OperatorResponse.p: Use the explanation shown in the message to determine the cause of the failure and take appropriate action to rectify the problem.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule {0}. Queue manager connection {1}. XAPrepare returned XA_RDONLY.

Explanation.p: The MQ XAPrepare function returned XA_RDONLY. Typically this means that earlier attempts to put messages to MQ were unsuccessful.

OperatorResponse.p: Check the destination of the mapping rule to ensure that it is able to receive messages, for example, check that a queue is not full.

Message.MsgText: Destination mapping rule {0}. Queue manager connection {1}. XID {2}. XARollback returned XA_HEURCOM.

Explanation.p: The MQ XARollback function returned XA_HEURCOM for a transaction of which ${IMA_PRODUCTNAME_SHORT} has no record. This happens when the transaction branch has been manually committed in MQ. The transaction will be ignored and the destination mapping rule will start.

OperatorResponse.p: Use MQ facilities to forget the transaction branch specified by the XID.
